---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';
import { authorPhotoExists } from '../utils/authorPhoto';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Josh English, full-stack software engineer at AWS."
>
  <div class="wrapper prose about">
    <p class="eyebrow">~ cat about.md</p>
    <h1>About</h1>

    {
      authorPhotoExists && (
        <img
          class="about-photo"
          src={SITE.authorPhoto}
          width="160"
          height="160"
          alt="Josh English"
          loading="eager"
          decoding="async"
        />
      )
    }

    <p>
      Josh is a full-stack software engineer at AWS. He didn't start out writing
      code. He just always liked taking things apart to see how they worked, and
      that eventually turned into a career. Outside of it, he's into finance,
      wrenching on motorcycles, collecting wine, and pretending to play golf.
    </p>
    <p>
      The actual entry point was a bootcamp at
      <a href="https://generalassemb.ly/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">General Assembly</a>.
      Since then he's written code at The Desire Company (fka desirelist), Fitch
      Solutions, and now Amazon Web Services. He's also chipping away at a Master's
      in Computer Science at Georgia Tech (OMSCS), mostly on nights and weekends.
    </p>
    <p>
      The spaces he keeps coming back to are blockchain, web3, fintech, and
      anything with a social-impact angle.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    padding-top: var(--space-xs);
  }
  .about h1 {
    margin: var(--space-2xs) 0 var(--space-m);
  }
  .about-photo {
    float: right;
    width: 160px;
    height: 160px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    object-fit: cover;
    border: 2px solid var(--border);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-s) var(--space-m);
  }
  @media (max-width: 30rem) {
    .about-photo {
      float: none;
      margin: 0 0 var(--space-s);
    }
  }
</style>
